remarks: A numerable set is strictly dominated by another iff their cardinalities are strictly ordered.  (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 30-Oct-2014.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 29-Apr-2015.)
statement: cardsdom2 $p |- ( ( A e. dom card /\ B e. dom card ) -> ( ( card ` A ) e. ( card ` B ) <-> A ~< B ) ) $.
